At 06:23 AM 10/28/2003, you wrote:

>I'll usually take out the #1 spark plug and stick the eraser end of a pencil
>down in the hole to verify #1 is all the way up. I do remove the valve cover
>and usually watch both valves

If you have a compression gauge, just screw it into No. 1 without the 
gauge. Hold your thumb over the hole and rotate until you feel the pressure 
forced out by the compression stroke. Continue turning to the timing mark. 
TDC No. 1, empirically.
